g.text: Unemployment rate and employment to population ratio in Greater Melbourne and the rest of Victoria

text.style: font-size: 14.00px; font-weight: bold; fill: #004676; font-family: Liberation Sans;

g.text: The unemployment rate in Greater Melbourne was 6.9 per cent while the rate in the rest of Victoria was 4.7 per cent in March 2021

text.style: font-size: 7.77px; font-style: italic; font-family: Liberation Sans;

g.text: Source: ABS Labour Force, Detailed (monthly). Note: most recent data is for March 2021. Data not seasonally adjusted. Smoothed using a 3 month rolling average.
